+
+$ ruff format --check services/home-miner-daemon/
+5 files already formatted
+
+$ bandit -r services/home-miner-daemon/ -ll
+Total issues (by severity): Medium: 1
+Files skipped: 0
+
+$ bash scripts/no_local_hashing_audit.sh --client apps/zend-home-gateway/index.html
+result: no local hashing detected
+exit 0
+```
+
+## Pending: Branch Protection
+
+Branch protection for `main` requires GitHub repository admin settings. This cannot be configured via files in the repository. After merging, the maintainer should:
+
+1. Navigate to repo Settings → Branches → Branch protection rules
+2. Add rule for `main`:
+   - ✅ "Require pull request before merging"
+   - ✅ "Require approvals" (set to 1)
+   - ✅ "Require status checks to pass before merging" — select: `test`, `lint`, `security`
+   - ✅ "Do not allow bypassing the above settings"
+
+Or via `gh` CLI:
+
+```bash
+gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/branches/main/protection -X PUT \
+  -f required_status_checks='{"strict":true,"contexts":["test","lint","security"]}' \
+  -f enforce_admins=true \
+  -f required_pull_request_reviews='{"required_approving_review_count":1}'
+```
+
+## Coverage Note
+
+The pipeline enforces 80% code coverage. Currently no test files exist in the repository, so the coverage requirement will fail until tests are added. The test job will pass only after tests are created (see plan 004 for test suite).
+
+## Recommendations
+
+1. **Create tests** — The test job will report "no tests collected" until test files are added
+2. **Add pre-commit hook** — Consider adding `ruff check` and `ruff format` as a pre-commit hook for local feedback
+3. **Coverage threshold** — Consider lowering to 0% until a meaningful test suite exists, then raise to 80% incrementally
